I have been told in the past that `<|` is preferred to `$`, so you might change these (and below) to head off that comment.

Given that the first 12 lines of these proofs are identical, it feels like there's a lemma missing. At the very least you could probably prove these as an `∧` and then split them afterwards into two lemmas.

Otherwise I have no complaints.
I can't really find a lemma to unify both of them (the 12 lines are just checking that the statements are rotation-invariant), so I proved the conjunction
